title: God Bless Pseudo Saturn

caption.text:
A few years ago I became obsessed with experiencing the Sega Saturn library for the first time, but was immediately disheartened when I realized how much money I’d need to spend to do so. Luckily, I figured out how to flash Pseudo Saturn to an Action Replay cart and burn any Saturn game I felt like playing. It’s a wonderful thing . 👍

mixer.com/ravagevision #mixer#mixerstreamer#mixerstreamers#mixerlove#mixergamer#mixercommunity##mixerfamily#watchmixer#gamer#gamers#gaming#gamingcommunity#gamerlife#gamersofinstagram#videogames#gamerguy#games#streamer#xboxonex#xboxgaming#

Space Invaders is finished!! This game first came out in 1978 and is considered one of the most influential games of all time. It basically invented the "shooter" genre, and went on to inspire other developers like Shigeru Miyamoto, Hideo Kojima and John Carmack.

It definitely inspired me growing up. I have always been a sucker for fun gameplay loops with the implication of a rich story just beneath the surface, and I loved imagining myself warding off an alien invasion. With this reimagining, I really wanted to sell the world it took place in. Stuff like the semi-fluid shield generators were my way of trying to respect classic mechanics while having it still feel like cool, cutting edge sci-fi.

The Easter eggs in this one are few, but some of my favorites. Hiding in the background are the spaceship and asteroids from the 1979 game "Asteroids" (I wanted to do a fun twist on the classic vector shapes), and the ship from "Lunar Lander" hanging out on an asteroid to the right. 
This is a new favorite of mine, really happy with how it turned out!

caption.text: I was cleaning out a closet today in search of old #technology when I found my original #rodemicrophones box.  Inside the forgotten box I had stored a few of the very first games I played and got work on early in my #voiceacting career. The very first game I voiced and also played on my PC was #bladerunner. ❤️. Great game! I got the job through a paper called #dramalogue and it was #SAG!!! Crazy how times have changed. It’s a game created by #westwoodstudios and it even had some of the original cast from the movie. 💕😎 I was very surprised and honored after a session to meet the actor who played  #eldontyrell , Joe Turkel.  It was a lucky way to start my #voiceovercareer in #videogames, I must say.  I thought I had lost the game . I squealed and was very excited that I found it! Soooo cool.😎 #jessicastrausvo #animation #narration #singing #gratefulheart #lostandfoundrecords #memories

caption.text:
Happy Tuesday Fam 🤗
.
Let's not forget that today is a gift but also an opportunity to tell the people in our lives that we love and appreciate them ❤️ it's so easy to get caught up in the rhythms of life from school, varsity and work that we forget to tell the most important people in our lives that we love them ❤️
.
But equally today is an opportunity to live the unloved, those who feel rejected, hurt and broken. Those who feel like they don't have a home. And especially to those who are too scared to speak about what they going through so they put on a brave face ❤️ to all of you, I'm praying for you and I love you ✌🏽
.
Get up, go out and love somebody, and go get lost on the way 👏🏽- it's a song but I forgot the name right now.

caption.text: For the love of god turn the sound on. @balenciaga #parisfashionweek

The last week has been brightened by the simplest, and most lovely of games - Untitled Goose Game. I never take the bad paths in games, but for once it's the only path and I get to be the best goose doing it. Thank you so much House House Games. P.S. Also just one of my favorite games now; it's very indicative of quality when the only criticism of a game is wanting more of it!
.
.
.
Art credits (not including first pic): 2+3 @chuckdrawsthings, 4 @celsiusgs (Twitter), 5 @thanksxu, 6 @milkytiddyboy, 7 @daffodilisart, 8+9 @Mero_Nyaa (Twitter). Also @huntydraws did a wonderful one you should check out; I'm honoring their request to not repost.
#UntitledGooseGame #GooseGame #Goose #VideoGames #CreditArtists

I have a concern for TLOU part II. What if Naughty Dog is tricking us and Dina isn’t the one who dies? What if Joel dies within the first act of the game and he’s just a part of Ellie’s conscience or something? Trust me,I really hope I’m wrong. Joel is one of my top favorite video game characters and I would hate to see the story for TLOU part II turn out to be that predictable. It just feels like Dina is a red herring because it almost feels too obvious that she dies,you know? Thoughts?

Words cannot express how amazing this weekend was. Easily my favorite convention I’ve ever been to! It was so nice being able to see friends both old and new, getting to hangout and worry about nothing but having a good time. It’s pretty incredible to think that it’s because of a website that it’s possible for all of us around the world to be able to come together for at least one weekend and see eachother in person!
I have the best friends in the world. Thank you for making this weekend one I will never forget! 
Until next time 💙
